Describe a creative person whose work you admire.
- Who he/she is
- How do you know him/her
- What creative things he/she has done
- Explain why you think he/she is creative

When talking about a creative person whose work I admire, I would like to mention Linus Torvalds, who is a Finnish software engineer best known for creating the Linux operating system.
I first learned about him when I started becoming interested in technology and programming. At that time, I discovered that many computers and servers around the world run on Linux, which made me curious about the person behind it. After doing some research, I realized how influential he is in the tech industry.

In terms of his creative work, he developed the Linux kernel, which is the core part of an operating system. What is truly remarkable is that he started this project as a personal hobby while he was still a university student. Over time, it grew into one of the most important open-source projects in the world. He also created Git, a widely used tool that helps developers manage and track changes in their code.

I think he is extremely creative because he didn’t just invent something new, but he also changed the way people collaborate. By making Linux open-source, he allowed programmers from all over the world to contribute and improve the system together. This idea has had a huge impact on modern software development.

What I admire most about him is his logical thinking and his ability to turn complex ideas into something practical and widely used. His work proves that creativity is not only about art or music, but also about innovation and problem-solving.

If I had the chance, I would love to learn more about his mindset and how he approaches challenges, because I believe it could inspire me in my career.

